# Documentation and workflow rules

Before changing code:

1. inspect relevant code and tests;
2. identify the smallest coherent change;
3. document assumptions;
4. add or update tests;
5. implement;
6. run targeted tests;
7. run the full verification build;
8. update documentation;
9. summarize changed files and limitations.

Update documentation in the same change as behavior.

Use fictional hostnames and environment-variable placeholders in examples.

Never commit real credentials, certificates, keytabs, principals, or internal hostnames.

Do not rewrite unrelated code.

Add an ADR for significant architectural changes.
